g.text: #0 The initial CPU boots from the ROM, but
it only execute a few instructions to configure
the PCIe end-point and enable the PCIe-PHY.
After this the CPU is put into sleep
#1 The external CPU complex boots. Eventually it will do
PCIe enumeration and discover the LAN966x end-point
#2 The external CPU will now neet to initialize the
Switch Core, PHYs and other. This is done through
the PCIe link. This configuration can be done by either
#3 Frame DMA is still used to move frames between the
CPU system and the queues in the switch core
